Algorithm LinearSearch(arr, target)
Pre: arr is an array, target is the element to be found
Post: return index if found, else return -1

1. if arr is empty then
       return -1
2. for i = 0 to length(arr)-1 do
       if arr[i] = target then
            return i
3. return -1
End Algorithm


(II)
Algorithm LinearSearch(arr, target)
Pre: arr is a list of elements, target is the element to find
Post: returns the index of target if found, else returns -1

start = 0
end = length(arr) - 1

For i = start to end do
    If arr[i] = target then
        Return i    // Found the element
    End If
End For

Return -1   // Element not found
End Algorithm


(III)
Algorithm LinearSearch(arr, target)
Pre: arr is an array, target is the element to be found
Post: return index if found, else return -1

Step 1: If arr is empty, return -1
Step 2: For i = 0 to length(arr)-1 do
         Step 2.1: If arr[i] = target, return i
Step 3: If target not found after loop, return -1
End Algorithm